> Factory fitment for a UK late bay with the Type 1 1600 engine was a
34PICT 3 and a SVDA distributor. Timing is set with hoses removed and plugged
to 7.5

That's correct. SVDA or plugging the retard line and timing at 7.5 is
a suggested modification for US buses too.

